The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing a low rank matrix from contaminated data, which is a common problem in machine learning, computer vision and data science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves manipulation of singular values, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
